HEADWORD: Cockleshell
<hw>Coc"kle*shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
of the shells or valves of a cockle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A light boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To board the <qex>cockleshell</qex> in those plunding waters.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Black.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cockloft</ent>⟦br⟧
